Again, I'm not a fan of maintain the document manually.

Patch Set 2:

As I mentioned this doc was written to standardize our backends API and docstrings for the methods. It's especially important now, because we have plans to implement another NoSQL backend on MongoDB (https://blueprints.launchpad.net/glance/+spec/enable-mongo-db, http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/meetings/glance/2015/glance.2015-03-26-14.00.log.html - 14:35:52 <nikhil_k> #topic NoSql backend support ( ajayaa )). So, this documentation is like a help for them, where it's said what they should implement.

Also, we have big plans for code refactoring in Liberty - to write or renew docstrings and after that make a tool to auto-check that all backends are in consistent state. So if one of the methods is changed, for example in sqlalchemy, it will tell to make the corresponding changes in the others (and in documentation too).

The next thing is about a picture. I'm going to write a tool to auto-generate those pictures. But the main goal to include it in the documentation now is it helped so much when I was implementing artifacts DB API. I had the same picture in front of me and I didn't have to remember what attributes are there.

Patch Set 2:

@Mike that is really helpful. if you could have pinged me with this earlier, that would have saved me a weeks of work. Anyway I will go through this to make sure I didn't miss anything.

Thanks,
Ajaya
